The '''Bilibino Nuclear Power Plant''' ({{lang-ru|Билибинская АЭС}} [{{Audio|Ru-Билибинская атомная электростанция.ogg|pronunciation}}]) is a [[Power station|power plant]] in [[Bilibino]], [[Chukotka Autonomous Okrug]], Russia. The plant is equipped with four [[EGP-6]] reactors.<ref>{{cite web |title=Russia: Bilibino |url=http://www.nti.org/db/nisprofs/russia/reactor/power/bilibino.htm |date= |work= |publisher=[[NTI]] |accessdate=5 September 2009 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090511020851/http://www.nti.org/db/nisprofs/russia/reactor/power/bilibino.htm |archivedate=11 May 2009 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> The plant is the smallest and the northernmost operating nuclear power plant in the world.<ref>{{cite book |last=Nuttall |first=Mark |date= |title=Encyclopedia of the Arctic |url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=Swr9BTI_2FEC&pg=PA241&dq=%22world%27s+northernmost+nuclear+power+plant%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0CCoQ6AEwAGoVChMI76Tgj6znyAIVyzkaCh1A9g0D#v=onepage&q=%22world's%20northernmost%20nuclear%20power%20plant%22&f=false |publisher=[[Routledge]] |page=241 |isbn=1-57958-436-5}}</ref> Plans to begin a shutdown procedure of the plant in 2019 have been announced,<ref>[http://regnum.ru/news/economy/2103335.html Билибинская АЭС на Чукотке будет остановлена в 2019 году]</ref> and it will be replaced by the floating nuclear power station ''[[Akademik Lomonosov]]''.<ref name=wnn-20161007>{{cite news |url=http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/WR-Work-starts-on-on-shore-infrastructure-for-Russian-floating-plant-0710165.html |title=Work starts on on-shore infrastructure for Russian floating plant |publisher=World Nuclear News |date=7 October 2016 |accessdate=12 October 2016}}</ref>
