'''John Twidell''' is Director of the AMSET Centre Ltd. and is a visiting lecturer at the Environmental Change Institute, [[University of Oxford]], and the School of Aeronautics and Engineering, [[City University, London]].<ref name="Fapesp">{{cite web |url=http://www.fapesp.br/materia/5071/pfpmcg/professor-john-twidell.htm |title=Professor John Twidell |publisher=Fundação de Amparo à Pesquisa do Estado da São Paulo (FAPESP) |accessdate=2009-05-01}}</ref>  He is Editor Emeritus of the academic journal ''[[Wind Engineering]]''.  He co-edited the 2009 book ''Offshore Wind Power''.<ref name=john>{{cite web |url=http://www.multi-science.co.uk/offshore-wind.htm |title=Offshore Wind Power |publisher=Multi-Science |accessdate=2010-02-12}} (primary source)</ref>

Professor Twidell previously held the Chair in [[Renewable Energy]] at [[De Montfort University]] and was Director of the Energy Studies Unit of [[Strathclyde University]]. He has served on the Boards of the British Wind Energy Association (now [[RenewableUK]]) and the UK Solar Energy Society, on committees of the [[Institute of Physics]] and as an adviser to the UK Parliamentary Select Committee on Energy.<ref name=john/> He has been a long-standing champion of wind energy.<ref>{{cite journal |last=Simms |first=Andrew |title=‘What I hope to see in the energy white paper’: two views |page=10 |date=March 2006 |journal=Science & Public Affairs |publisher=British Association for the Advancement of Science |issn=0268-490X |url=http://www.britishscienceassociation.org/NR/rdonlyres/1D1FCEBB-9129-4AA0-B6C3-8761BFD714BC/0/5019_SPAMarch.pdf#page=6 }}</ref>

