The '''Kisigmánd Wind Farm''' is a wind power project in [[Komárom-Esztergom County]], [[Hungary]]. It is owned and operated by [[Iberdrola Renovables]], and has an output of up to 50 [[Megawatt|MW]] of power, which made it the largest wind farm by power generation in Hungary when it was built.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.renewableenergyfocus.com/view/15716/iberdrola-secures-half-of-hungary-s-wind-energy-market/ | title=Iberdrola secures half of Hungary’s wind energy market | publisher=Renewable Energy Focus | date=8 February 2011 | accessdate=11 May 2017}}</ref>  It was Iberdrola's first wind farm in Hungary when it began operation in early 2009.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.renewableenergyfocus.com/view/1305/iberdrola-increases-q1-wind-production-clarifies-uk-position/ | title=Iberdrola increases Q1 wind production, clarifies UK position | publisher=Renewable Energy Focus | date=14 April 2009 | accessdate=11 May 2017}}</ref>

