The '''March 6–9, 1998 North American storm complex''', was a particularly powerful [[snowstorm]] originating on March 6. It was the biggest storm to hit [[Chicago]] since February 14, 1990, when 9.7 inches fell over two days. This storm dumped varying amounts of snow across the area. Chicago's [[Southwest Side, Chicago|Southwest Side]] was also hard hit, with 10.9 inches recorded at [[Midway International Airport]].

