{{Infobox Protected area | name = Morne Trois Pitons National Park | iucn_category = II | photo = File:Dominica Hiking Path.JPG | photo_caption = Hiking trail in the Morne Trois Pitons National Park | location = [[Dominica]] | nearest_city = | embedded1 = {{designation list | embed=yes | designation1 = WHS | designation1_date = 1997 <small>(21st [[World Heritage Committee|session]])</small> | designation1_type = Natural | designation1_criteria = viii, x | designation1_number = [http://whc.unesco.org/en/list/814 814] | designation1_free1name = State Party | designation1_free1value = Dominica | designation1_free2name = Region | designation1_free2value = [[List of World Heritage Sites in the Caribbean|Latin America and the Caribbean]] }} | coordinates = {{coord|15|19|30|N|61|19|00|W|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | area = 68.57 km² | established = 1975 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = }}
'''Morne Trois Pitons National Park''' is a [[World Heritage Site]] (since 1997) located in [[Dominica]]. This area was established as a [[national park]] by the Dominican government in July 1975, the first to be legally established in the country.<ref name=CCIH>{{cite book|last=Hailey|first=Adrian|title=Conservation of Caribbean Island Herpetofaunas Volume 2: Regional Accounts of the West Indies|year=2011|publisher=BRILL|isbn=9004194088|page=162|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QNdbVSDfF6oC&pg=PA162&dq=Cabrits+National+Park&hl=en&sa=X&ei=_FzZUoWsKcussQTKsICADg&ved=0CEMQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=Cabrits%20National%20Park&f=false}}</ref> The National Park is named after its highest mountain, Morne Trois Pitons, meaning mountain of three peaks. The park is a significant area of volcanic activity. Features within the part include the [[Valley of Desolation (Dominica)|Valley of Desolation]], a region of boiling mud ponds and small [[geyser]]s; the [[Boiling Lake]], [[Titou Gorge]], and [[Emerald Pool (Dominica)|Emerald Pool]].
<gallery> Emerald Pool Dominica.JPG|Emerald Pool and Waterfall Middleham Falls at Morne Trois Pitons National Park.jpg|Middleham Falls File:Morne Trois Pitons National Park, Dominica - jungle.jpg|Dominican Jungle File:Freshwater lake at Morne Trois Pitons National Park.jpg|Freshwater Lake </gallery>
